Changing the lenses on your camera will give

00:00:22.340 --> 00:00:27.159
you the ability to zoom or to shoot wide angle
or to shoot natural photography. I just happen

00:00:27.159 --> 00:00:33.290
to have small sampling of interchangeable
lenses for my SLR system. The first one I

00:00:33.290 --> 00:00:38.330
kind of want to show you about; this one is
really one of my favorite lenses. It's a 70

00:00:38.330 --> 00:00:48.910
to 210 zoom Nicor Lens. It's a fairly slow
lens. It only stops down to F4 to a 4. I really

00:00:48.910 --> 00:00:55.930
like this lens because it is pretty old. It
is razor sharp for SLR but it is like a pretty

00:00:55.930 --> 00:00:59.550
kind of standard lens and it gives me everything
that I need when I am in the studio shooting

00:00:59.550 --> 00:01:04.970
strobes. The second one I want to talk about
is also a zoom lens but the focal length on

00:01:04.970 --> 00:01:09.479
this lens isn't as long. This is a 35 to 70
and this is probably a little bit more of

00:01:09.479 --> 00:01:13.820
a flexible lens. It allows me to get a little
bit closer to my subject but to still be able

00:01:13.820 --> 00:01:19.220
to shoot wide, kind of wide angle and to be
able to zoom and play a little bit. The third

00:01:19.220 --> 00:01:23.649
lens that I want to talk to you about. This
